replies.comment info:
@Nick L (2/2)

This affects me and the beautiful state of North Carolina because we’ve experienced hurricanes in the past. We literally have a hockey team named the Carolina Hurricanes.  This is not the first time we’ve experienced hurricanes. Just a few years ago, we experienced Florence, one of the most devastating storms here. But nowhere near close to some other storms, and that was a category 5! If hurricanes become our highest risk still in 2040, I’m genuinely scared for my state. 

My headline for this graph is: Take a look at the highest climate risk in each region expected by 2040.
